reviews.text:
*Oct 14, 2018 update:
Happiness: The dipped chocolate Sundae cone take away is so good and cheap (HK$6). The staff at the icecream counter is nice.
Disappointment: I bought a fried chicken set meal using the self-order kiosk at 11:03am and had to wait for more than 35 minutes in line. The staff did not make good use of the POS system. The ticket numbers displayed on the screen did not match with the food available to be taken. Very messy managememt.
---
*March 30, 2018 update: The portion of macaroni is constantly smaller than that by other branches. Also the stock is not hot enough. 
---
Full of low-class and dirty customers, and the tables are not cleaned frequenty. No Mc Cafe. No drive-in. The only good is 24 hours open.
It's a Mac Donald duh ! What more to say
Good tasty for breakfast
you know what you are getting when you walk in. really need a review?

Food quality is standard junk. So, one star. Price is however low when compared with adjacent fast food restaurants.This justifies its upgrade to two stars, and no more. 
There are only a few restaurants at Hung Shui Kiu. This M Kee thus provides an acceptable choice.  
It is always packed with casual  people. This results in an unclean dinning hall, slow servicing counter and cashier. Though three self servicing boards are available for customers to buy food tickets, usually only one board can function. This may be this shop's tactics to minimize the pressure on its kitchen. Customers however need to toletate a longer waiting time before they can bite in the burger. All these reflect the shop's dissatisfory management.
